gomodel:SYNGO_383  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 1, 2. Used atomic force microscopy (AFM) on the calyx-type nerve terminal of the chick ciliary ganglion to localize single calcium channels. Calcium channels were tagged using a biotylinated form of the Cav2.2 specific venom peptide omega-conotoxin GVIA (b-omega-CTx). The labelled channels were visualized using avidin-coated 30nm gold particles. Controls used: untreated, b-omega-CTx treated without gold, and preblocking with untagged omega-CTx.\n\nNerve terminals were identified in vitro from structural clues together with staining using the vital dye 4-Di-2-Asp The location of the terminals was noted by their relation to an electron microscopy grid attached to the underside of the coverslip. A sketch was also made of the terminal and the surrounding cells and cell debris so that the calyx could be re-identified under the AFM.\n\n30/6/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Chick embryo ciliary ganglia (15-day-old) were dissociated and incubated\nwith enzymes for 150 min to increase the yield of isolated calyces. The preparation was plated on a poly-L-lysine-coated coverslip and incubated at 37°C in minimal essential medium (MEM) to allow the dissociated cells to attach." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_383" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9031" .

